# 86: Add Tests Suite for new-dev Node.js Container

https://github.com/darthjee/navi/issues/86

## Background

The new development backend (`new-dev/`) is a Node.js Express application that serves dynamic endpoints based on a YAML file. While the main application in `source/` already has a comprehensive test suite running in CI, the Express dev server currently lacks automated tests. To ensure reliability and prevent regressions, we need to add a dedicated test suite for the `new-dev` container and integrate it into the CI pipeline.

## Task

- Set up an automated test suite for the Express app in `new-dev/`.
- Tests must cover all endpoints and edge cases (valid requests, 404s, malformed input, etc).
- Tests must run automatically in CI, just like the main application's tests.

## Requirements

- Use a standard Node.js testing framework (e.g., Jest, Mocha, or Jasmine) and a HTTP assertion library (e.g., supertest).
- Place all test files under `new-dev/spec/` or a similar directory.
- Add a test script to `new-dev/package.json` (e.g., `yarn test`).
- Ensure the test suite can be run both locally and in CI.
- Update CI configuration to run the new-dev tests as part of the build.
- Document how to run the tests in the project documentation.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All endpoints in `new-dev/app.js` are covered by automated tests.
- [ ] Tests verify correct responses for valid requests and proper 404 handling for invalid routes/IDs.
- [ ] Running `yarn test` inside `new-dev/` executes the full test suite.
- [ ] CI runs the new-dev test suite and fails on errors.
- [ ] Documentation is updated with instructions for running and maintaining the tests.

